FBIS4-49717 "drchi090_p_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-090 Daily Report 6 May 1994 Central-South Region Guangdong Issues Circular on Price Controls Guangdong Issues Circular on Price Controls HK0905133694 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network in Mandarin 0400 GMT 6 May 94 HK0905133694 Guangzhou Guangdong People's Radio Network Mandarin BFN [Text] The provincial people's government recently issued a circular calling on all areas across the province to place a total of 25 daily necessities and services under price supervision and control. The 25 daily necessities and services placed under price supervision and control, as stipulated in the provincial people's government circular, are as follows: Rice, wheat flour, peanut oil, pork, eggs, milk, salt, soy sauce, mainland vegetables, detergent, coal, liquefied petroleum gas, coal gas, running water, electricity, public transportation, tuition and miscellaneous fees, child-care fees, medical fees, food and drink, rent, commodity residential quarters, hotel rooms, and so on. The circular stated: In order to place the prices of these daily necessities and services, those cities and counties that have not yet set up a grain-risk fund or a main non-staple food price regulation fund, should waste no time in setting up such funds, while those cities and counties that have set up such funds already, should take further steps to improve the relevant systems and measures and should employ more economic means to regulate and control market commodity prices.
